history.text: Hello
Hello! Have you seen the movie Catch Me If You Can?
No, I have not.
Have you? If so, did you enjoy the movie?
Leonardo DiCaprio, Tom Hanks, and Christopher Walken all star in Catch Me If You Can.
I have watched Catch Me If You Can. The director, Steven Spielberg, is a favorite of mine.
Are you a fan of dramatic crime films?

He is a great director and it sounds like the movie has a great cast. I like mysteries, so yes to the
 dramatic crime films.
Is this a crime movie?
You should definitely watch Catch Me If You Can. I highly recommend it. It received a 96% rating on Rotten Tomatoes.
Yes, it is a crime movie.
What's the plot?
Is it a violent film?
In 1963, a teenager named Frank Abagnale carries out a series of cons that are worth millions of dollars.
It is based on a true story, but, no, it is not a violent film.
From posing as a substitute teacher in his French Class to impersonating an airline pilot, Frank Abignale succeeds in stealing over $2.8 million.
It is an outstanding film. It really is.
That's good. I'm not a fan of violent movies. Wow, a teenage con stealing millions, that's pretty impressive.
It sounds like an interesting movie with a great plot and cast.
It is!
I'd like to see it sometime.
There is one particular scene that is uniquely interesting.
oh?
The scene is towards the end of the film. The conclusion of the film will keep you on the edge of your seat.
I won't spoil it for you, though.
Ok. Don't spoil it for me.
Thanks.
Remember that it is a true story.
I will tell you that the ending credits reveal that Frank has been happily married, has three sons, lives in the Midwest, and still earns a good living.
So it's a criminal who overcomes his criminal past to live happily ever after? That sounds nice.
As a criminal, Frank Abagnale does actually redeem himself in the end .
Who plays the character, Frank?
Leonardo DiCaprio plays Frank.
When did this movie come out?
Amy Adams and Nathalie Baye are also in the Catch Me If You Can.
The movie came out in 2002.
Well, this is going on my "to watch" list. Thanks for the recommendation.

uid2response.feedback: I did not have to read a document. My conversation went smoothly and the other user answered all my questions and actively tried to convince me to watch the movie, "Catch Me If You Can."
